HEADWORD: Alveary
<hw>Al"ve*a*ry</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Alvearies</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>alvearium</ets>, <ets>alveare</ets>, beehive, fr. <ets>alveus</ets>
a hollow vessel, beehive, from <ets>alvus</ets> belly, beehive.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A beehive, or something resembling a beehive.</def>
<rj><au>Barret.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The hollow of the external
ear.</def> <rj><au>Quincy.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alveated</ent>⟦br⟧
